translation.Name: Nautical Nuisance
translation.Description: Barnacles are starting to form on the Liberator's hull, but Rusty's joints are acting up too much to dive down and scrape them off. He'd appreciate if you can help out because given time they can cause quite a bit of trouble.

translation.Name: <color=mythical>Sparks</color>
translation.Description: While flying South over Jhavesk <color=uncommon>Ensign Cliff's</color> squad's helicopter took several electric shocks from a giant sparking zombie. If you're brave enough he's sure it'd be appreciated to kill it before it can cause more trouble.

translation.Name: <color=mythical>Scorched Earth</color>
translation.Description: Recently Norbert was helping out on a scavenging mission to Novobirsk when they ran into a gigantic "firebreathing" zombie. Unfortunately this means they can't clear it out for supplies until the zombie is slain.

translation.Name: <color=mythical>Aftershock</color>
translation.Description: During Peter's escape from Yekativurg he barely avoided a giant zombie that pounced from the air, slamming into the ground causing "miniature earthquakes". He hasn't been able to get it out of his mind and would really appreciate knowing it had been dealt with.

translation.Name: On Air
translation.Description: <color=legendary>Commander Laurence</color> wants to get the Russian radio towers working again to broadcast to any survivors still out there. You'll need a toolkit which he says Natalie down in engineering can provide.

translation.Name: The One That Got Away
translation.Description: If you happen to catch Wallace's nemesis the giant squid he'd love to see it! Keep in mind the chances are quite slim, it's very rare.

translation.Name: Getting the Word Out
translation.Description: For survivors without radios <color=legendary>Commander Laurence</color> plans to put up posters with directions to the Liberator. He suggests placing them in each town/city's police station.

translation.Name: The Squeaky Motor Gets the Grease
translation.Description: The ship's engine has been rattling quite a bit recently, but Natalie doesn't have the resources spare to fix it up. If you can find them for her while looting she'll take care of it!

translation.Name: Smuggler's Cove
translation.Description: If you think it's worth checking out <color=epic>Chief Brian</color> has given you permission to investigate the smuggling. He thinks if there is any base to it there'd be traces of a shipment somewhere along the coastline.

translation.Name: Coldcase
translation.Description: <color=epic>Chief Brian</color> suggests starting with Darren, Harry's bunkmate, on the bridge. It might also be worth searching through Harry's stuff, and Natalie might have seen something, and Roman might have overheard something... Suffice it to say he has a lot of suggestions.

translation.Name: The Conspiracy's Conclusion
translation.Description: <color=epic>Major Len</color> just received a transmission from the smugglers that seems to have originated from Silo 22 in the far North, but he suspects they actually used it as a relay station. If that's correct there should be a log in the command center which might reveal who sent it, and from where.

translation.Name: Memoir
translation.Description: Gwen accidentally lost her wedding ring overboard. She'd really appreciate if you can bring it back to remember her husband by.

translation.Name: Top Gun
translation.Description: Before taking to the skies you'll need a <color=rare>Fighter Pilot Outfit</color> and a replacement Jet Compressor. Andy thinks you can salvage a Compressor from the wreckage of the nuclear submarine West of the Liberator and retrofit it for the Jet.

translation.Name: A Fresh Coat of Paint
translation.Description: Rusty thinks the Liberator's name could use some touching up since it's starting to fade. Next time you're in Saint Petersburg he's pretty sure the hardware store might still have a bit of white paint.

translation.Name: The Secret Snack
translation.Description: <color=epic>Chief Brian</color> is craving for a few doughnuts, but doesn't want to be seen to fit the police stereotype. He wants this kept on the down-low, you know hush hush.

translation.Name: Research Recovery
translation.Description: As a side project Dr. Swanson is researching the virus and potential for a cure. The remains of a <color=legendary>Scorpion-7</color> cargo plane were spotted in the very far North, and she suspects that research capsules containing samples, notes, DNA, etc were strewn from the plane into the deadzone during the crash.

translation.Name: The Hunt for Jet Fuel
translation.Description: <color=rare>Lieutenant Oswald</color> is willing to give you a try scouting out a location, in this case an airport North-East of Moscow. This usually involves clearing out quite a few zombies, and then analyzing the environment to prepare a report determining which areas are worth securing.

translation.Name: Mass Production
translation.Description: Russia has many warehouses filled with old WWII and coldwar machinery, but this one in the North-West is of particular note. Satellite images from 6 years ago differ from newer data suggesting it was brought back into use as a factory, and <color=rare>Lieutenant Oswald</color> thinks it might have been producing new armored vehicles.

translation.Name: The Wolf's Den
translation.Description: Volk, the Russian word for wolf. <color=rare>Lieutenant Oswald</color> wants you to infiltrate what is essentially Russia's largest military base in the far North-West, easy right?

translation.Name: First Contact
translation.Description: This isn't the first time the <color=legendary>Coalition</color>'s been to Russia. Back in the organization's infancy a primarily Russian task force seized an offshore oil rig in the South-West as a proxy pending backup to reclaim the mainland, but something went wrong. <color=rare>Lieutenant Oswald</color> needs you to find out what.

translation.Name: W.M.D.
translation.Description: In the far North is a secret underground nuclear missile silo which has supposedly detonated, but aside from the radiation there's no evidence of explosive damage. <color=rare>Lieutenant Oswald</color> needs you to verify that the warhead is completely spent and can't be used again.

translation.Name: The Great Escape
translation.Description: T.Rickster is supposedly wrongly imprisoned, but insists you don't ask the security team about him. He's given you a blueprint for his favourite kind of cake and would really appreciate if you can bake it for him. He can't give you much now, but says he'll pay you back later.

translation.Name: The Ultimate Fishing Rod
translation.Description: Wallace needs a reinforced fishing rod to catch the illusive giant squid. He's given you a blueprint to craft it from a normal fishing rod.

translation.Name: Mysterious Papertrail
translation.Description: <color=legendary>Commander Laurence</color> needs an important note delivered to Rusty. He'd appreciate if you didn't say who it's from.

translation.Name: Gingerbread Army
translation.Description: Try out Sous-Chef Roman's new festive recipe. Combine flour, eggs and chocolate and bake in an oven for a flavourful surprise.

translation.Name: Festive Cheer
translation.Description: Use the Saw to harvest Candycane Fragments and create some decorations.

translation.Name: Christmas Eve
translation.Description: Apparently there have been presents scattered somewhere in Moscow, go and check it out!

translation.Name: Suspicious Snowballs
translation.Description: Some mysterious frozen water with explosive properites has started accumulating on the Liberator's deck. Harvest some samples for Doc Ernie to investigate.

translation.Name: <color=legendary>Coalition</color> Armory
translation.Description: Looking for military/ranger ammunition and trading surplus gear.

translation.Name: Leonard's Fresh Food Market
translation.Description: Part fresh, part stale army rations.

translation.Name: P.Riso's <color=#fa3200>Hot</color> Stuff
translation.Description: Not like stolen stuff, good stuff everyone wants! 97.5% satisfaction guarantee!

translation.Name: Saw
translation.Description: Tool used to cut down oversized Candycanes.

translation.Name: T.Rickster's <color=#323232>Blackmarket Smuggling</color>
translation.Description:
Everything you should be able to buy but aren't allowed to!
There's probably a good reason you're not allowed to, so don't think about that!

translation.Name: Portable Canvas
translation.Description: Always bring more paint than you'll need!

translation.Name: Artistic Pants and Apron
translation.Description: Just don't dirty yourself when making a mess.

translation.Message_0_Page_0: I'm in charge of our armory, keeping it stocked and ready for combat. We can always use more ammunition, so let me know if you'd like to trade!
Always a pleasure!
Hello!
Glad to hear it! Here are your <color=uncommon>Ensign</color> fatigues.

Darren?!<pause> It all makes sense now, being bunkmates Harry must've caught him smuggling and gotten thrown in with the cargo! As comms operator Darren was also in the perfect place to hide transmissions with the gang.
translation.Message_0_Page_1: I'll strip his rank and have him sent down to the brig. On a brighter note <color=epic>Major Len's</color> squad will be back soon, they captured the gang and rescued Harry. If you'd like to meet him he'll probably be recovering in his quarters!
translation.Message_0_Page_2: As usual you've done absolutely fantastic work, thank you!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Pleased to meet you <name_char>. You're welcome aboard, just keep in mind you're back in society so don't try and pull anything illegal.
translation.Message_0_Page_1: We're part of an international force formed in the wake of the outbreak called the <color=legendary>Coalition</color>. Our mission here is to rescue as many survivors, like you, as possible and unite to reclaim our home.

translation.Message_0_Page_0: I'm sorry, but we don't recruit <color=uncommon>Ensigns</color> sight unseen. If we notice you helping out around here there's a place for you in our ranks, however!
translation.Message_0_Page_1: Come to think of it we're looking for someone to help spread word of our presence here <pause>- if you're interested to give a hand talk with my first mate Laurence.

translation.Message_0_Page_0: I'm sure you won't. Here are your <color=rare>Lieutenant</color> fatigues.
And I yours. I'm sure we'll have many more adventures together! Here are your fatigues, congratulations <color=legendary>Major</color> <name_char>!

There are three main ranks to climb:
Major - Leader of a squad
Lieutenant - Deputy to a Major
Ensign - Soldier in a squad
translation.Message_0_Page_1:
Beyond that are the core members of the Coalition:
Admiral - Heads of state strategizing our global offensive
Captain - Leader of a contingent, like me
Commander - Right hand of a Captain, like Laurence here

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Uniform supply is one of <color=uncommon>Ensign Franklin</color>'s responsibilities, you can buy a replacement from him.

Thank you for bringing this to my attention!
*she pulls you aside*
translation.Message_0_Page_1: It's time you should know:<pause> Len's working for me. After they kidnapped Harry I asked him to go undercover and try to infiltrate their gang <pause>- his recent behaviour is all a ruse to convince the real traitor he's on their side.
translation.Message_0_Page_2: Due to his high rank and therefore access to rare supplies they were willing to work with him, even if they were suspicious of a trap. So far they haven't trusted him enough to reveal his accomplice on the ship, but thanks to your investigation I suspect the mole will let his guard down and contact the smugglers to rescue Len.
translation.Message_0_Page_3: You've done a great job so far. If you're discrete you have my permission to work with Len and form a plan to catch the real traitor!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Thank you! Let's see what it says.
translation.Message_0_Page_1: Awww so sweet...<pause> "Will you be my valentine? -Secret Admirer"

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Ah hello! I heard there was someone new on-board. I'm <name_npc>, in charge of this vessel and aiding any survivors we come across. You're one of the first we've met, what's your name?
translation.Message_1_Page_0: By all accounts you've shown yourself to be the embodiment of what we look for in an <color=uncommon>Ensign</color>. The rank is yours if you want it!
translation.Message_2_Page_0: You've been an exemplary <color=uncommon>Ensign</color>, and it's about time you were promoted! If you're ready I'm prepared to make you a <color=rare>Lieutenant</color>!
translation.Message_3_Page_0: I'm very proud of you <name_char>... <pause>You've done a stellar job and I think you're ready to lead a squad of your own as a <color=epic>Major</color>. What do you say?
translation.Response_2: Thank you, I won't let you down
translation.Response_3: I'm honored, I'll stand by your side <color=legendary>Captain</color>
translation.Response_4: I need some time to think about it
translation.Response_7: Can I get a replacement uniform?

translation.Name: Note - Dr. Behan #1
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_3: My new workstation at the outpost is turning out a lot better than I expected. The staff here seem to be warming up to me already, and Dr. Stevens even invited me to play chess earlier today! This lot's experiments are a step above the boring DNA splicing down South and for the first time in months I am feeling intellectually stimulated. Still, I miss Spot and the cold up here is something else, but the move was unavoidable for obvious reasons.
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_5: The shipment from HQ came in earlier than expected, more contract work for those executives at Big J. This one seems to be part of an even larger project, and I get the feeling they are splitting it up between the labs to make it harder for us to see the big picture. Not really sure what the consumer application is either, but hey, it pays the bills!

translation.Name: Note - Laura #1
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_3: They're acting like everything's normal, but I can tell ma and pa noticed it too. I remember growing up here, my whole life, my family, my friends in Montague... but the memories don't fit right... if that makes sense. This is MY diary, but reading back I don't feel like I wrote those things.

translation.Name: Note - Apology
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: I'm sorry, so so sorry... Our past bioweapon contracts were never used so I didn't think twice about this one. If you're reading thi

translation.Name: Note - Dr. Behan #3
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_3: The local government is definitely onto us, I got evicted yesterday! With them snooping around our lab the boss is making plans with HQ to relocate. Right now they're thinking either Washington or BC, but a few of us are getting sent off to other facilities early to work on other projects. I'm assigned to "hallucinogenic weapons" codename "berrybush" up in the Yukon, should be interesting. Apparently it's part of some work for Big J, and they've already begun testing on wildlife.
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_5: I'm not sure what to do with Spot, he's not suited to a cold climate. If the location replacement seems like a nice family I'll leave him with them.

translation.Name: Note - Polysol #1
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: Local ID: "Earth"
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_3: Universal Time: 18510975918
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_6: Scans suggest the majority of the planet's foliage contains chlorophyll with an estimated value in the billions of credits, and ~71% of the surface consists of oceans with an estimated value in the millions of credits. We recommend keeping a patrol of this system to prevent pirates from attempting to steal any, at least until they can defend themselves.

translation.Name: Note - Military #4
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_3: Somebody has to keep a record of what actually happened, otherwise anything can become history. We didn't know of course, it was just a few blips on the radar - could easily have been a suprise attack, and we gave them fair warning! Although in hindsite I doubt their comms use the same tech as ours. The one we recovered went down in New Mexico. The other one's lost, but I doubt there were any survivors. None of us expected it to be a flying saucer! The government's trying to play it down from the public, and the official account is that we rescued them after they crashed into an unidentified object.
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_5: It's not my place to reveal any of this, and we can't change the past... The way they're handling this rubs me up the wrong way though... I think I'll quitely retire, almost at that age anyway. Maybe we'll move someplace nice.

In this artical we investigate their experimentation on wild animals and how they've been adding chemicels to keep you coming back! continue on here about the contract + observations + etc
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_5: also seems kind of ironic I'm writing this in a Big J fastfood, but wow these blueberry pancakes are amazing :)

translation.Name: Russia Note - Janitor
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_3: I felt it following me again, and every time the lights flicker I see something out of the corner of my eye. As I write that the lights have gone out in the hall... I'd best go check the fuses.

translation.Name: Russia Note - ATC
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: May 22nd 07:18
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_3: The plane we just landed - flight 106 - isn't responding, and appears to have been on autopilot. Ground crews are preparing to expediate the passengers' departure in-case of emergency.
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_6: Flight 106's occupants seem to be carrying an extremely fast-acting virus infecting everyone in the area. Security is moving to intercept and everybody else is being evacuated to Moscow.

translation.Name: Russia Note - Big J
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_3: That businessman from Big J came around today trying to buy us out again - they even raised their offer! He said we're the only ones still holding out... I know we could really use the money, but I can't imagine how disappointed Dad would be if I sold the family business especially to a chain brand like that.

translation.Name: Russia Note - Scorpion-7
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: Within a few hours of listing it an e-mail came in from an anonymous buyer offering way more than its worth! Said they're a collector of "artifacts" like that and to let them know directly if we find any more. Selling that piece of junk made more than this entire dig will and corporate doesn't need to know anything about it! The truck which picked it up was blank except for the license plate "SCRP-7B", aside from that I still have no idea who it was.

translation.Name: Russia Note - Trainyard
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: I haven't talked to anyone from the military before, but this morning I was sleeping in only to have soldiers pull me out of bed and drag me down here to work the turntable. They wanted to take out good ol' Ivan. He's been parked here since World War II aside from the occasional display, but still runs just fine. I think I overheard one of them say something about blowing up train tunnels - either I'm hearing things or something's wrong.

translation.Name: Note - Mission Briefing #1
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_3: Intel suggests they have experienced a containment leak, so you are tasked with moving in earlier than expected. Exercise extreme caution, remember that these guys are heavily armed. If given the opportunity take any tangos captive for interrogation later.

translation.Name: Russia Note - Military
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: May 22nd 10:25
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_3: We just lost contact with the rail cannon team. I fear the worst, but from their last transmission it sounds like their mission was a success - all exits are now blocked... We're trapped here with the infection.

translation.Name: Russia Note - Submarine
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: 03:02 - Temperature Stable
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_3: 03:03 - Temperature Stable

translation.Name: Russia Note - Silo
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: Orders have come from the highest level to launch the warhead... at Moscow. They say that the city is being stormed by a dangerous virus, and that sacrificing it will save our country. I signed up to protect our motherland, not destroy it! I'm burning the message and cutting communications in the hopes that cooler heads will prevail and seek a cure rather than wiping out those pour souls. Should they try to attack and force a launch I'm afraid I'll have no option but to sabotage the missile.

translation.Name: Russia Note - Coalition
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: It's been a flurry of activity the past few days so I haven't had the chance to write an entry - Russia has joined the Coalition, and I've been assigned to set up a forward operating base. After surveying the coastline we picked a relatively accessible oil rig to secure and begin helping survivors. Scouts are reporting that a large region North of Moscow is completely irradiated, so we'll have to be careful of the fallout. Reinforcements are already on their way to help us take a headquarters on the mainland, and several nuclear submarines in the area are rendezvousing with us here.

translation.Name: Russia Note - Mafia
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: Word on the street is that the military's in a frenzy with some sort of disease going round, and they're completely spread out trying to quarantine it. The boss has given the command to capitalize on this chaos... These are going to be a crazy few days.

translation.Name: Russia Note - Kilroy's Journal
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: Fascinating... Once we cracked the first several symbols the rest came very easily. From what we can tell so far these etchings seem to be a recording of the tribe's history, of particular note is this large faded icon. It's composed of runes representing nighttime, whispers, a harvest and what they describe in the text as a "soulcrystal" of immense power activated by some sort of ritual. It was so powerful that even the most pure-hearted exposed would gradually be swayed to ruthless ambition. After a horrible incident the tribes were forced to unite and fracture it, each secretly encasing a piece in stone such that no one person should know the location of all the fragments. This tribe buried their part in a tomb guarded by their spirit ancestor "Anastasia". I'm interested to see if we can find this relic, however I'm sure it was purely of superstitious or traditional importance.

translation.Name: Russia Note - Lab #1
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: 13:42: No positive response to our modified vaccine prototypes, it's adjusting too fast. If anything they seem to be further mutating compared to the control - one is growing acid glands, another is generating electricity and another even taking on fireproof properties.

translation.Name: Russia Note - Lab #2
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: I can't believe we're rebooting this project, we've tried bombarding it with all kinds of radiation, electrifying it, blowing it up, but nothing. Still, if this is what they came here for it must be important, and they do genuinely seem to think it will work if we can crack it, but personally I'm starting to question whether maybe the extended cryosleep scrambled their brains.

translation.Name: Note - Mission Briefing #2
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_3: Details are still sparse, but reports of a highly contagious virus are coming in from across the country. Before going dark the federal government ordered the destruction of Confederation Bridge to prevent the virus from spreading here. Your unit is assigned the bridge, whichever munitions you need are at your disposal.

I don't think that's right because she would have told me, so I cycled down to their farm. Well at least where their farm used to be. Someone in a biohazard suit told me the road was off limits and turned me around, but I saw construction equipment and a giant hole where the crops used to be. I hope Laura's okay...

translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: Tensions are high with the Coalition ramping up its presence in the area. Those greedy tryhards have almost finished stealing the entirety of downtown for themselves. Everything's better with the government gone - we can't sit idly by while they attempt to fill its place.

translation.Name: Peaks Note - Syndicate Plan
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: Enough is enough. We're going to launch a three pronged strike into the heart of the Coalition presence here kicking them out for good.
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_5: Due to dense walker presence in the city they leave their blast doors closed so we're not getting in there. The bridge entrances are a different story, however - they're left open the majority of the time. Your team will drive through both entrances simultaneously before they can react and provide covering fire from the overpass.
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_8: The sewer system is unguarded so your team can slip in and attack heavily armed with the element of surprise.
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_11: You'll be posing as survivors taking refuge through the main city entrances. You won't be able to smuggle in many weapons, but when the chaos starts you'll be able to begin the offensive from the inside.

translation.Name: Peaks Note - Coalition Syndicate Awareness
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: We're no closer to locating the local rebel group's base other than that it must be near the mountain. They're evidently planning something big though - I advise we remain on high alert and consider going on the offensive.

translation.Name: Peaks Note - Shuttle Crash
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: Our most recent shuttle launch has failed, crashing landing into Cologne 3 clicks east of here. Your squad is assigned to locking down the area and beginning the recovery process. We need to know what went wrong and salvage as much of the equipment as possible. Don't reveal this information to your team, but be cautious: it was carrying extremely radioactive material which might cause a much more powerful secondary explosion.

translation.Name: Peaks Note - Shuttle Launch
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: Docking clamps OK
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_3: Flight systems OK

translation.Name: Peaks Note - Shuttle Plan
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: Everything's on schedule for the next shuttle launch. We're the only facility still operational - Schwarzwald went dark several days ago, so it's on us to get the last few shipments to the station. The pressure's high and it's starting to affect morale. Humanity's future rests on our shoulders.

translation.Name: Peaks Note - Shuttle Load
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: They airlifted the next shuttle in today, it's just resting on the runway now. These sprints are super taxing - we'll be working round the clock to set it up for launch.

translation.Name: Peaks Note - Castle
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: If you're here to loot the castle don't bother. We tried blasting the front door but it's covered in thick iron plates. In fact all the windows and doors are shielded. It must be some sort of security system.

translation.Name: Peaks Note - Bielefeld
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: I could swear I went camping last week in Bielefeld... I must be losing my mind. I'm going to see a counselor.

translation.Name: Peaks Note - National Redoubt
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: Orders have come in to enact the National Redoubt. We're to move all troops to the Western mountains and refocus efforts on Plan B.

translation.Name: Peaks Note - Dino
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: While blasting into the limestone some of the workers uncovered what looks to be a kinda dinosaur skull. We're not sure how to handle it - this calls for tools more precise than anything we've got on site.

translation.Name: Peaks Note - Train
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: We couldn't slow down in time before hitting a rockslide on the tracks and derailing. This whole hill is unstable - I'm worried the tunnel is going to collapse. Everyone else was more severely injured in the crash so I've been chosen to go looking for help. I hope I find it quickly because I'm not equipped to be fighting any infected.

translation.Name: Peaks Note - Lost
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: It feels like I've been trapped down here for ages and I've been going in circles. I'm scared I'll never find a way out. It was just a normal hiking trip until I fell into that pit. They always told me I should bring a buddy! Now nobody knows I'm here. If you find this... please take care of my cats.

translation.Name: Peaks Note - Logging
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: It'd been a few weeks since my last contact with anyone in town so I took the trip in to restock supplies and see Jerry. I didn't go all the way in 'cause everyone was milling around in the streets. Looking through my binocs it was chaos, they looked extremely disheveled and I saw a few folks eating a corpse. There were multiple crashed cars abandoned on the way there and back. I don't know what to do or try next, but one thing's for sure: something horrible's happened.

translation.Name: Peaks Note - Checkpoint
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: This posting is soooo boring. Even if something did come through the tunnel I doubt it could climb the blockade.

translation.Name: Peaks Note - Bodies
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: Fence off a 400 square meter area and dig a 10 meter deep hole. In an effort to curb the spread of the plague we're going to start cremating infected corpses in the pit.

translation.Name: Peaks Note - Brew
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: Today I got word other breweries in the region are also picking up on berry mixes. I've started a trend!

translation.Name: Peaks Note - Flood
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: Assemble a team for an away mission to the dam. Bring enough explosives to cripple it and fortify the upper causeway until we give further orders. If worse comes to worst we'll blow the dam and flood the valley.

translation.Name: Note - Present Delivery
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: Hockey Stick
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_3: Fire Axe

translation.Name: Note - Cookie Recipe
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: Ingredients :
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_3: 1x Flour
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_10: 3. Put dough on tray and form into little men
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_11: 4. Put cookies in oven and bake at 180C
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_12: 5. Remove the tray from the oven when golden brown

translation.Name: Russia Note - Relay
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: Msg: Okay Len, sounds like you're in some hot water, we'll work something out and be in touch soon about picking you up.
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_3: Source: "Karl" 62865-3 Radio
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_6: Msg: Seems like Len's legit after all, there's a big investigation into him at the moment and they're getting pretty close. You might want to get him out of here before he spills the beans.

translation.Name: Platinum Ring
translation.Description: Used for the special Hawaii quest.

translation.Name: Gyro Makeshift Vehicle
translation.Description: Empty frame ready to be built upon.

translation.Name: Mushroom
translation.Description: There is poison in these mushrooms!

translation.Name: Raft Makeshift Vehicle
translation.Description: Empty frame ready to be built upon.

translation.Name: Roasted Mushroom
translation.Description: By cooking the mushroom you removed the poison!

translation.Name: Mushroom
translation.Description: There is poison in these mushrooms!

translation.Name: Shark-Tooth Sword
translation.Description: From the jaws of the sea's most fearsome beast.

translation.Name: Hawaii Note - Ruins
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: Msg: We found a strange altar today. It appears  to be a switch or lever for something. When we touched it symbols on the altar lit up and the ground shook as if plates of rock were shifting underground.
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_3: Source: "Hannah"

translation.Name: Hawaii Note - Aegis 1
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: We knew it was more than a pharmaceutical company when frigate upon frigate of armed soldiers started to arrive daily. The military tried to intervene but it was simply too late. Aegis had too much firepower. I think there's still hope though. Word around the island is that the remnants of the coastguard have set up a safehaven to the south. I'm going to begin my journey to seek it out in the morning.

translation.Name: Hawaii Note - Aegis Security
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: Primary Objectives: Secure foothold at the laboratory and obseratory. Maintain security until the laboratory technicians have had time to complete harvesting and testing the possible vaccination materials.

translation.Name: Hawaii Note - Aegis Lab Tech
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: Primary Objectives: Set up mining and laboratory facilities once security forces have locked down the mountain. Begin harvesting and refining the vaccine materials. Find test subjects and begin testing the vaccines as soon as possible. Report back all findings.

translation.Name: Hawaii Note - Aegis clue
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: Security forces have been reporting sightings of the turned appearing in pools of magma. We haven't confirmed and sightings on caught them on any recordings. The lab techs assure me the air down here is safe but I'm not sure I trust anything the company says anymore...

translation.Name: Hawaii Note - Aegis Observatory
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: The scouting teams found another alter today inside the volcano. It is however currently unreachable due to lava flow. I will report back when I can confirm progress.

translation.Name: Hawaii Note - Doctors Office
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: We've been noticing more and more cases of sporatic violent tendancies. This is starting to appear similar to the outbreak in Washington.
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_4: It appears our hypothesis was correct. The infection has somehow spread to the island.

translation.Name: Hawaii Note - Akoni
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: They've been holding us here for days! Even though the ship is lovely I can't take much more of this! Why haven't we docked yet? I'll have to go ask the crew again.

translation.Name: Hawaii Note - Military Outpost
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_3: We've lost communications with Alika base and require a unit to head down and re-establish contact. Keep your head on a swivel soldier, we don't know what to expect down there.

translation.Name: Hawaii Note - Facility
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: A cargo plane just crashed a few hundred meters from the facility. We're starting to take on water and may need to evacuate. I'm going to go assist the repair crew.

translation.Name: Hawaii Note - Aegis 2
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: An Aegis truck stopped our group today. They put handcuffs on one of us and the rest scattered. I was too scared to look back amidst all the gunfire. I don't even know how many escaped. I'm going to head back to our base under the turbines and wait for the rest to return. I hope I'm not alone now...

translation.Name: Hawaii Note - Aegis 3
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: FROM: Sgt.Gilmore F.o.b. highrise
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_4: Scouts reported Aegis forces entering the mountain near the junkyard with hostages. Current surveys show no cave entries in the area but we know Aegis has been trying to access the ruins for weeks now. Recommend redeploying scouts to investigate further.

translation.Name: Hawaii Note - Unyielding 1
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: A T T E N T I O N   S U R V I V O R S !
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: We have established a safezone on the southeast coast near the memorial. We have food, water, shelter and warm beds.  Everyone is urged to join us and help humanity survive this outbreak.
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_4: Together we will stand strong.. We are the united, We are the Unyielding!

translation.Name: Hawaii Note - Cave Survivors
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: Journal entry.... Not sure how many days it's been anymore...
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: Was another rather boring night until Josiah started screaming that he could see a ship. We all saw it. Something shining extremely bright on the water just beyond the lighthouse. A few of us grabbed packs and ran but by the time we got there whatever we saw had vanished. We should consider setting some flares along the coast for the next time. It will certainly reveal our position to Aegis but just might be worth it for a shot off the island.

translation.Name: Hawaii Note - Aegis 4
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: FROM: HQ
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_4: Our destroyer has just been rammed by Aegis forces and communications are down. The entire area is highly radioactive due to the chemicals the Aegis frigate was carrying. No rescue mission will be possible
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_5: Furthermore we can expect no more support any time soon. Food and ammunition supplies are already running dangerously low.
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_6: Orders are to abandon the base, regroup with local Coastguard and await further orders. Godspeed

translation.Name: Hawaii Note - Aegis Botanist
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: They're here for the mushrooms I'm sure. The ancient culture here refers to them as a cure all. I'm going to have to investigate this myself and retrieve some samples. The dark cave systems around here are rich with them. Hopefully I won't need to wander far.

translation.Name: Hawaii Note - Boat Captain
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: First Entry: There was a serious outbreak onboard this morning causing a few passengers to become
translation.insanely: aggresive. We've quarantined the infected and requested an emergency docking in Hawaii.
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_4: Second Entry: The infection has spread through the lower floors of the ship and panic is taking hold of the passengers. We can see the shoreline now. Just a few more minutes...
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_6: Final Entry:  We're dead on the water. Almost everyone onboard is infected now. The final crew members are boarded up on the bridge. We're considering swimming for shore but we can see explosions in the distance. I pray whatever has plagued our vessel hasn't also hit the island...

translation.Name: Hawaii Note - Hospital
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: I've been studying these rare spotted mushrooms and it seems they have a similar effect to our current vaccines. Even more so when refined. This will prove useful as we run low on stock. My current estimations suggest we'll be out of treatments for the public within the week.

translation.Name: Tiki Altar #3 - On
translation.Interact: The heat behind this wall is intense [{0}]

translation.Name: Help Arnold stock the Armory!
translation.Description: Arnold is making an inventory of the Armory and needs you to grab him a few things!

translation.Name: Bake a cake!
translation.Description: Bill wants you to bake him a cake for his wife's birthday!

translation.Name: Find ingredients for Chef Larry!
translation.Description: Larry wants to lift the spirits of all the survivors at base. He wants you to find him ingredients so he can bake a Jade Pie!

translation.Name: <color=mythical>Electrifying</color>
translation.Description: While driving through Pahala <color=epic>Major Lee's</color> squad took some electric shocks from a giant sparking zombie, injuring one of his mates. He would like you to find and kill the zombie, so that no one else can get hurt!

translation.Name: <color=mythical>Is it me or is it hotter than usual!</color>
translation.Description:
While doing a supply run through the airport Commander Barlow's squad bumped into a dragon
I mean fire breathing zombie! He would love it if you could deal with the zombie! Fire is dangerous!

translation.Name: <color=mythical>Is that an earthquake?</color>
translation.Description: While making their way here, <color=legendary>Commander Barlow</color> and a few others felt a large quake in the ground. They thought it might have been the volcano erupting, but discovered a monsterous zombie. He wants you to travel to Keokea, but be careful, this thing tears up the ground and won't hesitate to throw it at you!

translation.Name: Find Botanist supplies!
translation.Description: Betty wants to get the garden up and running at the base, but needs a few things to do so!

translation.Name: Find new tools for Pete!
translation.Description: Pete broke some of his tools so he needs you to find him some new ones!

translation.Name: Find Car parts!
translation.Description: Danno really loves his car and wants to fix it up! He wants you to find him a battery and a tire!

translation.Name: Find supplies for Doctor Elliot!
translation.Description: Doctor Elliot needs medical supplies so she can keep treating the wounded!

translation.Name: Hidden Aegis Facility!
translation.Description: Sarah has had confirmed reports of Aegis kidnapping lone survivors but the Unyielding have had no idea where they were being taken. Gain entry to the Aegis facility within the mountain and locate their laboratory.

translation.Name: Lost Camera!
translation.Description: A scout claims he took photos of a hidden entryway into the mountain. We've been struggling for weeks to locate Aegis's hidden facility. The scout said he dropped it in a pile of rubble while fleeing the junk yard!

translation.Name: Find Coconuts
translation.Description: Jeff wants you to find him some coconuts. He wants to spruce his house up a bit!

translation.Name: Missing Friend Pt. 2!
translation.Description: In Hannah's letter she explained that she escaped to her grandfather's lighthouse. Head over to Tadaaki Light and see if you can find Hannah!
translation.Condition_0: Look for Hannah at Tadaaki Light! {0}/1

translation.Name: Find Fishing Rod
translation.Description: Freddy lost his fishing rod and seems really upset about it! He wants you to find him a new fishing rod!

translation.Name: Missing Friend!
translation.Description: Neil was investigating La Luna Kahiko with his friend Hannah to the West of here, but got over run by zombies, and had to split up. He wants you to go back to La Luna Kahiko and see if she might still be there, or if there could be any evidence of her still being alive!
translation.Condition_0: Find Evidence that Hannah is still alive {0}/1

translation.Name: Find Hangglider!
translation.Description: Harry doesn't know how to fly, so he wants you to find him a hang glider. At least he can fly one of those!

translation.Name: Find Splint
translation.Description: Stan took a bit of a tumble when exploring the cave and broke his leg. He needs you to find him a splint so he can get out here!

translation.Name: Giant Starfish!
translation.Description: Captain Reginald was sailing over just West of The Akoni and spotted a giant starfish that crawled under the coral reefs. He wants you to swim down there and bring the starfish back!

translation.Name: Lou's Muse!
translation.Description: Lou was a performer on the Akoni when everything went to chaos. He forgot his precious ukulele on the stage. He would love if you could go get it for him.

translation.Name: Make a BLT Sandwich
translation.Description: Bob has a craving for a BLT sandwich and would like you to make him one!

translation.Name: Find Bio Sample!
translation.Description: <color=legendary>Captain Norton</color> sent some scouts to check out the area. They discovered some busted open waste barrels with some kind of chemical in them. Head up the hill just past the construction yard and grab us a sample!

translation.Name: Find Fuses!
translation.Description: <color=legendary>Captain Norton</color> is in need of some fuses, but is unable to leave the outpost. He heard you could find a box of them at the wind turbines North East of Pahala!

translation.Name: <color=mythical>Clean Sweep</color>
translation.Description: A distressed group of surviving military soldiers has been discovered in Kailua-Kona. Unfortunately, the horde size is swarming, so extracting them safely will be difficult. This is the bruteforce option. You'll be taking on a large horde that includes several large special infected.

translation.Name: <color=mythical>Dangerous Distractions</color>
translation.Description: A distressed group of surviving military soldiers has been discovered in Kailua-Kona. Unfortunately, the horde size is swarming, so extracting them safely will be difficult. This is the distraction option. Set up five distraction beacons while remaining undetected by the infected presence. Killing any zombies will result in your detection and the destruction of the beacons.

translation.Name: Fuse Box!
translation.Description: Thomas was installing the fuses you gave to <color=legendary>Captain Norton</color> earlier, but was overrun by zombies and had to come back before he could turn the radio tower on. He wants you to head over to Haiku Stairs and turn on the fuse box to the radio station

translation.Name: Relay Race
translation.Description: <color=uncommon>Ensign 'Chitchat' Winston</color> requires your aid so that he can contact the <color=legendary>Coalition</color>. You'll have to gather 4 deployable radio relays from the Ailani before setting them up at Airport, the lighthouse North of the Akoni, Mauna Kea Observatory, and Alika Base.

translation.Name: The Military Base
translation.Description: <color=uncommon>Ensign Stuart</color> wants you to infiltrate what is essentially Hawaii's Coast guard HQ in the far North-East of the Island, easy right?

translation.Name: The search for ports!
translation.Description: <color=uncommon>Ensign Stuart</color> is willing to give you a try scouting out a location. He wants you to check out Aouli Harbor. This usually involves clearing out quite a few zombies, and then analyzing the area for any other potential hazards!

translation.Name: City Living
translation.Description: Hilo is one of the larger cities on the Island. <color=uncommon>Ensign Stuart</color> wants you to scout this location for supplies! Preferably medical supplies and food!

translation.Name: Science!
translation.Description: <color=uncommon>Ensign Stuart</color> wants to know what all is being researched in the lab at Holokai Harbor. He needs you to clear out any zombies, and then check the lab for any left behind research!

translation.Name: Waikoloa
translation.Description: In the far North is another port city. <color=uncommon>Ensign Stuart</color> thinks this location would be good for getting supplies safely accross the Island!

translation.Name: Crash Down
translation.Description: <color=epic>Major Mac Alastair's</color> squad bailed before the plane went down just Northwest of Holokai Harbor. Your mission is to clear the harbor of infected before extracting the submerged munitions.

translation.Name: Spare Parts
translation.Description: <color=uncommon>Ensign 'Chitchat' Winston</color> requires some spare parts from wireless communication devices to repair his radio.

translation.Name: Find supplies for Chuck's raft!
translation.Description: Chuck wants you to find him some supplies so he can build a raft to get off this Island!

translation.Name: <color=legendary>Coalition</color> Stockpile
translation.Description: Looking for military/ranger ammunition and trading surplus gear.

translation.Name: Flower Finder
translation.Description: Find a flower then bring it to me on the island just west of the Akoni.

translation.Name: My Precious
translation.Description: It is a small platinum ring. I dropped it somewhere along this path, it couldn't have gone far!

translation.Name: All Shiny
translation.Description: In its time down here, the ring seems to have lost its shine. Could you find me some <color=uncommon>chemicals</color> I'd be able to clean it with?

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Glad to hear it! I hereby give you the rank of <color=uncommon>Ensign</color>.
Pleased to meet you <name_char>. You're welcome here any time, just keep in mind this is a civilized outpost, and we will not tolerate any disturbances!
translation.Message_0_Page_1: We're a rag tag group of survivors formed in the beginning of the outbreak called the <color=legendary>Unyielding</color>. Our plan here is to colonize as many survivors as we can so we can try to survive this outbreak together!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: I'm sorry, but we don't recruit <color=uncommon>Ensigns</color> without first seeing what you can do. If we notice you helping out around here there's a place for you in our ranks, however!
translation.Message_0_Page_1: We are looking for someone to help getting some things done around here! <pause>- if you're interested, make sure you talk with <color=legendary>Commander Barlow</color>, and <color=epic>Major Lee</color>.

translation.Message_0_Page_0: I'm sure you won't. Here you are now officially a <color=rare>Lieutenant</color>.
Excellent! We currently don't have any uniform for you. None the less congratulations <color=legendary>Lieutenant Commander</color> <name_char>!

There are three main ranks to climb:
Lieutenant Commander - Leader of a squad
Lieutenant - Deputy to a Lieutenant Commander
Ensign - Soldier in a squad
translation.Message_0_Page_1:
Beyond that are the core members of the Unyielding:
Admiral - Highest rank achieved in the coast guard, like myself.
Captain - Chief of staff
Commander - Right hand of a Captain, like Barlow here

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Hey there! I heard there was a new face around here. Welcome, my name is <name_npc>! I am in charge of this outpost, here to aid any survivors that may still be on the island. As you can see we have already had quite a few survivors show up. Now that I have introduced myself, how about your name?
translation.Message_1_Page_0: By all accounts you've shown yourself to be the embodiment of what we look for in an <color=uncommon>Ensign</color>. The rank is yours if you want it!
translation.Message_2_Page_0: You've been an exemplary <color=uncommon>Ensign</color>, and it's about time you were promoted! If you're ready I'm prepared to make you a <color=rare>Lieutenant</color>!
translation.Message_3_Page_0: I'm very proud of you <name_char>... <pause>You've done a stellar job and I think you're ready to lead a squad of your own as a <color=epic>Lieutenenant Commander</color>. What do you say?
translation.Response_2: Thank you, I won't let you down
translation.Response_3: I'm honored, I'll stand by your side <color=legendary>Admiral</color>
translation.Response_4: I need some time to think about it
translation.Response_7: No I think that is all!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Please find them. We need to stock up the armory!
Thank you so much! Now we can fight off more zombies!
I am just making an inventory of our stock!
translation.Response_1: I found the ammo and guns you needed!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: It would be great if you could make one for me, I have been craving a BLT like crazy lately.
Thank you so much!<pause> Mmm.. This is sooo good!
This tank doesn't really work, but it sure is a good deterrent!
translation.Response_1: I made that BLT for you!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Please bring me the cake. It would make her birthday fantastic!
Thank you so much! This will make her birthday the best day ever!
Isn't it a lovely day!
translation.Response_1: I baked that cake for you!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Today is my birthday!
Please bring me those seeds, we need them to keep surviving here!
Thank you, Now I can start filling the garden!
The flowers are so pretty here on the island!
translation.Response_1: I found the supplies you needed!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Be very careful when grabbing this, a few others have gotten sick just from trying to get close to those barrels!
Excellent work! I'm not sure how you did it, but the outpost is truly greatful!
Perfect, I'm going to get to work on checking all these to make sure none of them are duds!
As soon as you find those fuses, bring them straight back to me. We might not be able to find any others!
Hello, I'm <name_npc>! I have a few things you could help with, if you are up for it!
translation.Message_1_Page_0: Good, gonna need these fuses if we want to get communications back up and running!<pause> I have something else you could help with, if you are interested.
translation.Response_2: I found those fuses for you!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Please find them. I can't do anything without those tools!
Thank you so much! Now I can get back to building!
I love the smell of the ocean!
translation.Response_1: I found the tools you needed!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: I hope you can find all those ingredients, I would really love to bake a pie for everyone!
Thank you so much! This should lift everyone's spirits!
Hi there, I'm Chef Larry, glad to see a new face around here, welcome!
translation.Response_1: I found the ingredients you needed!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Thank you! Your efforts are much appreciated!
The sooner you deal with that zombie the better!
Greetings <name_char>! <name_npc> at your service! I have a task for you if you are interested!
translation.Message_1_Page_0: Now that you have defeated that zombie, I've got another mission for you if you'll take it.
translation.Response_2: I killed that big zombie for you!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: I'm sure you won't have a problem with this one either! You seem pretty skilled!
Excellent work! You should go see <color=epic>Major Lee</color>! I think he was looking for someone to help him out!

No where is safe anymore..
Not here
...
Not even over there!

Please bring me those parts, I love my car too much to leave her!
I need a battery and 1 tire. I have a flat, and she won't start!
Thank you, I can bring my car back to life again!
I like football, how about you?
translation.Response_1: I found the car parts you needed!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Please find everything on that list, I would do it myself but there is too much to do here!
Thank you so much! This is really gonna help a lot!
Just a few days and you should be feeling fine!<pause> Hi there, are you injured?
translation.Response_1: I found the supplies you need!
translation.Response_2: I'll be ok, you seem like you have your hands full!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: We need that radio tower up and running again. It will help us with our efforts in trying to reach the rest of the world!
Perfect, we should now be able to make contact with the <color=legendary>Coalition</color>,<pause> hopefully!
<name_char>! Just the person I wanted to see! I have a lot of work to do around here, but I could always use a hand!
translation.Message_1_Page_0: Anything to report?
translation.Response_2: I turned on the fuse box!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: I am the communications expert! I do all things radio, plus I love to talk! I guess that is why I got the nickname "Chitchat".
Hello, I'm <color=uncommon><name_npc></color>. I think <color=epic>Major Mac Alastair</color> would like to speak with you!
translation.Message_1_Page_0: Listen to this! *Static* . . Thi- . . This is Sergeant Hale, How co- *Static* Hello? Is anybody out there?
translation.Message_1_Page_1: *Static* . . . *Static* This is Operation Mahiole, code holo aku I repeat, code holo aku ...
translation.Message_1_Page_2: It seems very militarisic, which is odd as they have been overrun for a long while now. I'll try contacting him, go inform <color=epic>Major Mac Alastair's</color>
translation.Response_5: All relays are up and running.

translation.Message_0_Page_0: The Ailani is contaminated with some biohzard material, take proper precautions.
Stellar! Just give me a minute <pause>.<pause>.<pause>.
translation.Message_0_Page_1: *Static Crackling* It's alive! Good work, I can start scanning and broadcasting on the Coalition frequencies, hopefully we can make contact very soon!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Here you go. <pause> Be more careful, we only have a narrow window here.
Excellent. Alika Base is probably your best bet to find these items.
Give me a minute and I'll have this radio up and running!
Ah, so you've noticed it too. <pause> It could be a variety of things, but I'm assuming it is a mix of trauma and hope.
translation.Message_0_Page_1: The Unyielding has provided hope for them all, for us too. I guess, would you rather dwell on the horrors and mistakes of the past, or move forward, reinvent yourself, and stay optimistic for the future.

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Me? I am technically a standard rifleman, but I like to put my extensive doctor training to use in the field as well.
Hello, I'm <color=uncommon><name_npc></color>. I think <color=epic>Major Mac Alastair</color> would like to speak with you!
translation.Message_1_Page_0: Hello <name_char>!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Depends who you ask, but I am officially the second in command of this squad. My position is support gunner, and my hobby is in anything that goes boom.
It is not as much as it looks, but we do have enough that we could exchange some of our surplus.
Good choices. I'll seeya around.
Hello, I'm <color=uncommon><name_npc></color>. I think <color=epic>Major Mac Alastair</color> would like to speak with you!
translation.Message_1_Page_0: Hello <name_char>!
translation.Response_3: That's a lot of supplies you got there.

translation.Message_0_Page_0: My role? Ha, I am the designated marksman and ballistics expert.
Hello, I'm <color=uncommon><name_npc></color>. I think <color=epic>Major Mac Alastair</color> would like to speak with you!
translation.Message_1_Page_0: Hello <name_char>!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: I'm very happy with the weather we are having lately!
Please bring them back as soon as you can!
Thank you so much! Now I can make a whole set of tropical drinking cups!
I really hope you find her!

Thank you! The letter says she had to run, but she would head to her grandfather's lighthouse. I remember her telling me that her grandfather ran the Tadaaki Light! Could I trouble you for one more favor?
Anything to report?
translation.Response_1: I found a letter addressed to you!
translation.Response_3: She wasn't there, but I found this note addressed to you!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Please see if she is at Tadaaki Light! Let me know if you find anything!
Thank you for helping me! This note is quite facinating. I wonder what to make of it!
Please bring me a red hang glider! It has to be red though, that's my favourite color!
Aw Gee thanks! Now I can at least pretend to fly!
The sky is so blue today!
translation.Response_1: I found you a red hang glider!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Today is the day I am gonna catch me the big one!
Sure Max...<pause> That's what you say every day!
Please bring one back as soon as you can, I have nothing better to do but fish, it is my life!
Thank you so much! Now I can hone my fishing skills some more!
I have terrible luck with fishing!
translation.Response_1: I found you a fishing rod!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: I'm keeping an eye out for any survivors out there!
This uniform was granted to me by my superior officer for my hardwork and dedication to the <color=legendary>Coalition</color>.
translation.Message_0_Page_1: Incase you have not heard, the <color=legendary>Coalition</color> is an international force that was formed during the outbreak. These 4 soldiers behind me make up the rest of my squad and are also all well respected <color=uncommon>ensigns</color> of the Coalition.
translation.Message_0_Page_2: Our mission is to aid as many survivors, such as yourself, as possible and unite to take back our home. It is this mission that brought us here, to Hawaii! Unfortunately, in the process our plane crashed leaving us stranded.
translation.Message_0_Page_3: With that said, we could use an extra set of hands. Earn trust amongst the Unyielding and introduce yourself to my squad, then we can discuss further work.

translation.Message_0_Page_0: While you keep the horde busy, <color=uncommon>Nitro</color>, <color=uncommon>Needles</color>, and <color=uncommon>Siren</color> will rescue the trapped soldiers. Goodluck out there, you'll need it.
Goodwork out there, you handled yourself well. The other team arrived about an hour ago, you should go say hi to the new arrivals.
A word from the wise, use some proper diving gear. Seeya soon soldier!
Goodwork! I think Chitchat over there could use a hand if you have the time.
*Sigh* Alright, I'll deal with it.
Unfortunately, I have neither the authority nor the supplies to officially recruit you. However, if you prove to be trustworthy we could use a helping hand.
<color=uncommon>Chitchat</color> has triangulated the postition, it appears the contact is coming from Kailua-Kona.
A military broadcast!? That is impossible, they were overrun ages ago! <pause> . <pause> . <pause> . <pause> Well if it is so, we better help them out.

We'll activate all four of the beacons once you are clear of the area.  Meanwhile, <color=uncommon>Nitro</color>, <color=uncommon>Needles</color>, and <color=uncommon>Siren</color> will rescue the trapped soldiers. If you alert the horde, the beacons will be disabled requiring you to retrieve new ones from <color=uncommon>Chitchat</color>.
Goodwork out there. The other team arrived about an hour ago, you should go say hello to the new arrival.

Yup, it has been, whew, I dont know how long now. We have been trying with no luck to contact a nearby Coalition craft. <color=uncommon>Chitchat</color> over there is our comms expert, but he can only do so much with the scrap bucket he boldly calls a radio.
Greetings! You must be <name_char>, new survivors are a rare sight, word of your arrival spread quickly. I'm <color=epic><name_npc></color>, good to see a fresh face around here!
translation.Message_1_Page_0: Anything new to report, <name_char>?
translation.Response_7: <color=uncommon>Chitchat</color> has found local military presence on the radio.
translation.Response_11: Sir, Mayor Ekko has been infected.

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Good luck! If you find it, be careful, those zaps really hurt!
Impressive! You have made it safer to travel through Pahala, which greatly helps our efforts! Thank you!
Welcome to the Unyeilding Headquarters. I'm <name_npc>! We could always use more helping hands around here.
translation.Response_0: My name is <name_char>! How can I help?

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Of Kailua-Kona, although I guess was would be more accurate. When everything started falling apart, Sergeant Hale and his team were sent to protect me and other important figures. Unfortunately, as time went on our numbers shrunk until just Hale and I were left.
translation.Message_0_Page_1: *Sigh* . I wish he had made it too. I guess he won't be needing this sidearm anymore, and nor will I, so take it. I would give you more for your courage but unfortunately Hale had most of the supplies on him.

translation.Message_0_Page_0: You must be <name_char>, thank you for your efforts. Unfortunately, during our escape I got infected. Could you tell <color=epic>Major Mac Alastair</color> for me?
translation.Message_1_Page_0: You must be <name_char>! I owe you a great debt, thank you.
translation.Response_2: I will notify him right away.

translation.Message_0_Page_0: I really hope you find it! I'm still very upset I left it behind!
Thank you so much! I thought I would never see it again!
Really glad I found this place, feel much safer now!
translation.Response_0: Anything I can help you with?

translation.Message_0_Page_0: I really hope you find it!
Thank you so much! I shall name him Patrick!
I'm very happy to be here!
Look for anything we may be able to use as intel. We're looking for survivors, research, supplies... anything really.
Excellent work! I am going to have to run a bunch of tests on this sample. We can only hope Aegis may have figured out a cure, and hopefully that is exactly what is in this tube!
Yes! These pictures are exactly what we've been looking for. I bet with some explosive we could get through that door...
We really need that camera back before Aegis finds it!
You have been clearly making a name for yourself here <name_char>! I'm <name_npc> Lead Scientist for the Unyielding!
translation.Message_0_Page_1: I have been studying this bio sample you brought back! I am beginning to think that Aegis might have something to do with the outbreak! I have a mission for you!
translation.Message_1_Page_0: Now that you have found the camera, I've got a much more important matter for you to assist with.
translation.Response_5: I found that other bio sample!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: I'm hoping there'll still be a few functional military vehicles and supplies leftover. Maybe even a couple of new coast guard outfits for some of the survivors here!
Partially looted? Figures, Aegis probably already cleaned the place out!
Not expecting you to find much supply wise, but if we can secure this location, it may be a good spot for transporting goods around the island!
Glad to hear you didn't have too many problems, this location will be perfect for getting supplies to us from the other side of the island!
Good luck! Keep and eye out for any medical supplies and food!
Interesting, a mechanic shop and pharmacy? sounds like it might be worth sending a team over for supplies in the future.
Find as much evidence about the science facility that is there! I am curious to know if we can use it to our advantage!
What on earth could they have been researching down there! Hmm, I may need to send another party over there to have a closer look!
Yet another harbor point we could use for supply runs!
Great work! We will have to send a boat over there to grab some supplies!
I've picked up a location for you to scout out, would you be interested in taking care of it?
translation.Message_1_Page_0: I've got another location for you to check out, but it's a bit farther away. Interested?
translation.Message_2_Page_0: I could use your help scouting out another location, if you are interested!
translation.Message_3_Page_0: This location would be key, but according to an old report there have been sightings of a rather large zombie. Interested?
translation.Message_4_Page_0: I think it's time we check out Holokai Harbor. I think there is more to that harbor than meets the eye!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: I'm keeping an eye out for more information on that bio sample you brought <color=legendary>Captain Norton</color>! What on earth were those Aegis people up to!
translation.Message_1_Page_0: I'm keeping busy keeping the lights running around here, and checking the charts for good locations to investigate!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Me too. <pause> He was a good man, they all were. <pause> My squad was protecting a group of mostly local politicians. Overtime, the numbers fell. I guess this makes me the lone survivor, and a failed mission.
translation.Message_0_Page_1: Well, thank you for the rescue. I figure you expended a fair share of bullets out there, so here, you can have my excess. I'll see you around.

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Here I was thinking I was screwed, but then out of nowhere came those boys dressed in blue! I hear you are what made it all possible, impressive.
My leg hurts! If I don't get that splint, I'll never get out of this cave alive!
Thank you so much! I can finally get out of here and see the sun again!
It's really dark down here!
translation.Response_2: Good thing you have a head lamp!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: I need everything on that list for my raft!
Thank you so much! Now I can finally get off this island!
I think it has been 3 years... no wait, maybe 4!
translation.Response_1: I found the stuff you need for that raft!

translation.Message_0_Page_0: My boyfriend convinced me to take a vacation in Hawaii...<pause> We've been stuck here ever since...
translation.Message_1_Page_0:
What!?!?! Oh my god!!!
I.....
translation.Response_0: Not the worst place to be stuck.

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Awesome, I'll see you there!
Thank you! *Turns toward Amanda*
translation.Message_0_Page_1: Amanda you've become the largest and best part me. You've changed me more than I ever thought possible and made me realize that all of our dreams can come true. When I imagine my future, the only thing I see for certain is you. I love you more than anything I've ever known, with every ounce of my being...
translation.Message_0_Page_2: I told you I was going to ask you this when we got to Hawaii, and here we are...
translation.Message_0_Page_3: Amanda Jade Hubler, will you marry me?

translation.Message_0_Page_0: Oh, thank you! If you happen to find it, please bring it to me immediately. Goodluck!
I can't believe we actually found it! Thank you so much!
Thank you so much! I'll be here when you get back.
Fantastic! I should be able to make it look brand new again.
I've been down here for days searching for a very important lost heirloom. Could you please help me find it?
translation.Message_1_Page_0: Hello! Think you could lend a hand?
translation.Message_2_Page_0: Thanks for you help. If you'd like to see why I've been so busy, meet me on the island just west of the <color=rare>Akoni</color>. Oh, and bring a <color=uncommon>flower</color> from the Unyielding stronghold garden!
translation.Message_4_Page_0: She's just been beeping since I asked her...
translation.Response_1: Is this what you're looking for?
translation.Response_6: Sure! I'll get that flower and meet you there!
